{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"97e01f6a-b115-4434-8981-f2c81ef48366","content":"No files found in the working directory — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your ContentPage root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is the single addition of:\n```\nx:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\nThis tells the XAML compiler the type of `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding ...}` on this page is resolved **at compile time**.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**2. Enable strict mode in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- In your .csproj <PropertyGroup> -->\n<StrictMode>true</StrictMode>\n```\n\nOr, to specifically fail on binding issues:\n\n```xml\n<WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n```\n\n| Warning | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| `XC0045` | Property not found on the `x:DataType` type |\n| `XC0022` | No `x:DataType` specified (uncompiled binding) |\n\nWith these settings, a typo like `{Binding Thme}` becomes a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n**3. Opting out locally** — if a binding must be dynamic (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate` whose type varies), disable compiled bindings for that node:\n\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding SomeProp, x:DataType=x:Null}\" />\n```\n\n## Summary\n\n- Add `x:DataType` pointing to your ViewModel type → bindings compile.\n- Add `WarningsAsErrors` for `XC0045`/`XC0022` → typos and missing `x:DataType` break the build.\n- No changes needed in `SettingsViewModel` or code-behind.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"42098140-c519-40f0-882a-345a86bcb2bf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking me to help convert a hypothetical SettingsPage.xaml to use compiled bindings. Since there are no files, I should provide guidance on how to do this conversion and explain how to catch binding errors at build time. Let me give a clear, practical answer with code examples.","outputTokens":827,"requestId":"9BD8:2441A9:5F9C853:6ACCB29:69EC0DF4"},"id":"d8d1c3d2-9f0b-4730-9f49-1669ad07e52c","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:44.890Z","parentId":"019d993d-9f43-42c0-a049-e314a48da9bc"}
